reviewText:
Early Access Review

I met the lead artist of this game at an expo at my local science center. He and I had a nice conversation about this game and some ideas for it.

Otherwise, Tacopocalypse is a very fun and fast-paced car game, I cannot wait for the game to leave Early access!

reviewText: Early Access Review\n\nI have to say this is one of the all time great being overshadowed by Triple AAA dissapointed. This gave me more fun than Tom Clancy the Division and COD BOP 3 combined. The developer influence from Rocket League, Tony Hawk and Jet Star Radio has allowed the game to become a combination of the three and flourish as it own game. So far all review so far have been extremely good and this is no difference. This game is true fun which is all you want from one, you can play with friend, high replayablilty, great soundtrack and more. Nothing to prove. Game of the Year Award. Viva Del Tacopocalyse.

reviewText:
Early Access Review

Tacopocalypse is a mechanical blast from the past featuring tricks and scoring fromTony Hawks, the delivery aspect of Crazy Taxi, and the car mechanics of Rocket League... but let's not forget that incredible soundtrack.

Playing this early build hints that this title has SO MUCH potential to be great with the right love. Maybe future releases could feature objectives like the old THPS? Maybe we could see an online mode? I could go on with how giddy this throwback is getting me.

reviewText:
Early Access Review

You can wall ride and grind rails with a car. Need I say more? Okay, I'll say a bit more. ;)

PROS:
Crazy Taxi meets Tony Hawk Pro Skater in this beautifully colored cartoony playground of skateboard-cars. Not to mention the word's ending so everything's exploding! This game features awesome graphics, fun gameplay, local multiplayer, multiple game modes, fluid controls, and innovative mechanics. I can go on and on!

CONS:
I want to run people over and throw tacos at their corpses.
